cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper explores the social quality of community structures formed across Twitter users. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper investigates the effectiveness of different content models for approximating social connection structures. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze user-generated content on Twitter. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper examines social communities and their properties on Twitter. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper investigates the effectiveness of different content models for predicting social links.
